n seeking post-secondary education as well.</p> <p>According to a ministry service plan report, the number of aboriginal students enrolled in post-secondary institutions rose from around 24,000 in 2009-10 to 24,862 in 2011-12. Looking further back, those who were awarded university credentials rose from 2,100 students in 2005-06 to 2,634 in 2009-10.</p> <p>Reno hopes others will get involved and the trend continues, due to the increased opportunities for post-secondary aboriginal graduates.</p> <p>\"For aboriginal people, a lot of the doors have been closed before or how to navigate post-secondary is not immediately clear when you don&apos;t have a role model there before you to guide you,\" she said.</p> <p>\"Now it&apos;s about opening those doors and securing those places.\"</p> <p>-30-</p>\n   ',NULL,NULL,NULL,'none',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Fresh',NULL,'News','News',NULL),(207,0,0,'RCMP to participate in Touch a Truck, Beresford, N.B.','text/html','http://www.rcmp-grc.gc.ca/nb/news-nouvelles/releases-communiques/12-09-27-115902-eng.htm','City',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,13,'The RCMP in New Brunswick is participating in the second annual Touch-a-Truck event to be held on September 29, 2012, in Beresford, N.B.\n',1348775057,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Thu, 27 Sep 2012 12:02:04 -0330',NULL,'Royal Canadian Mounted Police in New Brunswick',NULL,'The RCMP in New Brunswick is participating in the second annual Touch-a-Truck event to be held on September 29, 2012, in Beresford, N.B.\n',NULL,NULL,NULL,'none',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Fresh',NULL,'News','News',NULL),(208,0,0,'Shemogue man pleads guilty to producing marihuana, Shemogue, N.B.','text/html','http://www.rcmp-grc.gc.ca/nb/news-nouvelles/releases-communiques/12-09-26-151939-eng.htm','City',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,13,'A 51-year-old Shemogue, N.B. man has pleaded guilty to charge of production of marihuana under the Controlled Drugs and Substances Act