mployees',NULL,'\n    CUPE workers at Royals Roads University have voted 96% in favor of strike action. The strike mandate comes after more than two years without a new contract.\n   ',NULL,NULL,NULL,'none',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Fresh',NULL,'News','News',NULL),(627,0,0,'CUPE Workers Send SFU a Message &amp;ndash; Negotiate Now!','text/html','http://cupe.ca/bargaining/workers-send-sfu-message-negotiate-now','Canada',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,7,'\n    SIMON FRASER UNIVERSITY&#8212;CUPE&#8217;s 1,020 support workers at SFU have had enough. After more than two years of fruitless talks at the bargaining table, CUPE Local 3338 members have voted overwhelmingly in favour of strike action.\n   ',1348939090,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Fri, 28 Sep 2012 12:26:00 -0400',NULL,'News | Canadian Union of Public Employees',NULL,'\n    SIMON FRASER UNIVERSITY&#8212;CUPE&#8217;s 1,020 support workers at SFU have had enough. After more than two years of fruitless talks at the bargaining table, CUPE Local 3338 members have voted overwhelmingly in favour of strike action.\n   ',NULL,NULL,NULL,'none',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Fresh',NULL,'News','News',NULL),(628,0,0,'Economic Fundamentals:  How do we measure economic growth and price changes?','text/html','http://cupe.ca/economics/economic-fundamentals-measure-economic','Canada',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,7,'\n    We hear about the economy growing, shrinking, or stagnating (but rarely taking a break). What are the main economic indicators and what do they measure? What does that mean?\n   ',1348939090,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Fri, 28 Sep 2012 12:01:00 -0400',NULL,'News | Canadian Union of Public Employees',NULL,'\n    We hear about the economy growing, shrinking, or stagnating (but rarely taking a break). What are the main economic indicators and what do they measure? What does that mean?\n   ',NULL,NULL,NULL,'none',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Fresh',N