 Ken Georgetti, and he is urging premiers and territorial leaders to pressure the federal government to reform Employment Insurance.</p>\n<fieldset class=&quot;fieldgroup group-issue&quot;><legend>Related Content</legend>\n   Related Issue:&amp;nbsp;\n  \n      \n          Budget Analysis    \n       \n          Jobs &amp; Economy    \n       \n          Unemployment Insurance    \n     \n   Related Campaign:&amp;nbsp;\n  \n      \n          1238    \n     </fieldset>\n<p><a href=&quot;http://www.canadianlabour.ca/national/news/georgetti-says-recession-far-over-canada-s-unemployed&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;>read more</a></p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,'none',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Posted','266','News','News',NULL),(633,0,0,'CUPE 2262 members in Nelson still without a contract','text/html','http://cupe.ca/bargaining/2262-nelson-contract','Canada',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,7,'\n    NELSON, BC&#8212;Workers at the Nelson and District Community Complex (NDCC) continue to seek a fair and reasonable collective agreement as rotating strike action continues this week in Nelson.\n   ',1348939090,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Thu, 27 Sep 2012 13:32:00 -0400',NULL,'News | Canadian Union of Public Employees',NULL,'\n    NELSON, BC&#8212;Workers at the Nelson and District Community Complex (NDCC) continue to seek a fair and reasonable collective agreement as rotating strike action continues this week in Nelson.\n   ',NULL,NULL,NULL,'none',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Fresh',NULL,'News','News',NULL),(634,0,0,'CLC condemns coup in Honduras','text/html','http://www.canadianlabour.ca/national/news/clc-condemns-coup-honduras','The Canadian Labour Congress (CLC) condemns the overthrow of democracy by the military in Honduras and supports the call of the Organization of American States (OAS) for the immediate;Canada',NULL,NULL,342,NULL,NULL,NULL,16,'\n   Region:&amp;nbsp;\n  \n      \n          National    \n     <p>The Canadian Labour Congress (CLC) condemns the overthrow of democracy by the military in Honduras and supports the call of the Organization of American States (OAS) for the immediate, safe and unconditional return of its democratically-elected constitutional president, Manuel Zelaya. The CLC urges Prime Minister Harper to add our nation&#039;s voice to the growing calls from governments around the world for the Honduran military and public institutions to respect democratic norms, the rule of law and the Honduran constitution by ensuring President Zelaya&#039;s safe return to power.</p>\n<fieldset class=&quot;fieldgroup group-issue&quot;><legend>Related Content</legend>\n   Related Issue:&amp;nbsp;\n  \n      \n          Threats to Democracy    \n     </fieldset>\n<p><a href=&quot;http://www.canadianlabour.ca/national/news/clc-condemns-coup-honduras&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;>read more</a></p>',1348939092,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Thu, 02 Jul 2009 04:00:00 +0000',NULL,NULL,NULL,'\n   Region:&amp;nbsp;\n  \n      \n          National    \n     <p>The Canadian Labour Congress (CLC) condemns the overthrow of democracy by the military in Honduras and supports the call of the Organization of American States (OAS) for the immediate, safe and unconditional return of its democratically-elected constitutional president, Manuel Zelaya. The CLC urges Prime Minister Harper to add our nation&#039;s voice to the growing calls from governments around the world for the Honduran military and public institutions to respect democratic norms, the rule of law and the Honduran constitution by ensuring President Zelaya&#039;s safe return to power.</p>\n<fieldset class=&quot;fieldgroup group-issue&quot;><legend>Related Content</legend>\n   Related Issue:&amp;nbsp;\n  \n      \n          Threats to Democracy    \n     </fieldset>\n<p><a href=&quot;http://www.canadianlabour.ca/national/news/clc-condemns-coup-honduras&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;>read more</a></p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,'none',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Posted','267','News','News',NULL),(635,0,0,'CLC President says forget working group','text/html','http://www.canadianlabour.ca/national/news/clc-president-says-forget-working-group','Unemployed workers are being badly hurt by the government delaying needed improvements to Employment Insurance;Canada',NULL,NULL,342,NULL,NULL,NULL,16,'\n   Region:&amp;nbsp;\n  \n      \n          National    \n     <h3>Fix EI now</h3>\n<p>OTTAWA - Unemployed workers are being badly hurt by the government delaying needed improvements to Employment Insurance, says Canadian Labour Congress President Ken Georgetti.</p>\n<p>He was responding to an announcement by Prime Minister Stephen Harper and Opposition Leader Michael Ignatieff that they will set up a working group to meet over the summer and consider changes to EI. Georgetti says, &amp;quot;We know what has to be done to fix EI. Putting off changes for months does not help unemployed workers or their communities.&amp;quot;</p>\n<fieldset class=&quot;fieldgroup group-issue&quot;><legend>Related Content</legend>\n   Related Issue:&amp;nbsp;\n  \n      \n          Unemployment Insurance    \n     </fieldset>\n<p><a href=&quot;http://www.canadianlabour.ca/national/news/clc-president-says-forget-working-group&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;>read more</a></p>',1348939094,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Wed, 17 Jun 2009 04:00:00 +0000',NULL,NULL,NULL,'\n   Region:&amp;nbsp;\n  \n      \n          National    \n     <h3>Fix EI now</h3>\n<p>OTTAWA - Unemployed workers are being badly hurt by the government delaying needed improvements to Employment Insurance, says Canadian Labour Congress President Ken Georgetti.</p>\n<p>He was responding to an announcement by Prime Minister Stephen Harper and Opposition Leader Michael Ignatieff that they will set up a working group to meet over the summer and consider changes to EI. Georgetti says, &amp;quot;We know what has to be done to fix EI. Putting off changes for months does not help unemployed workers or their communities.&amp;quot;</p>\n<fieldset class=&quot;fieldgroup group-issue&quot;><legend>Related Content</legend>\n   Related Issue:&amp;nbsp;\n  \n      \n          Unemployment Insurance    \n     </fieldset>\n<p><a href=&quot;http://www.canadianlabour.ca/national/news/clc-president-says-forget-working-group&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;>read more</a></p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,'none',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Posted','268','News','News',NULL),(636,0,0,'Citizens protest Colombian president&apos;s visit to Ottawa','text/html','http://www.canadianlabour.ca/national/news/citizens-protest-colombian-president-s-visit-ottawa','The Canadian Labour Congress and affiliated unions joined people from human rights;Canada',NULL,NULL,342,NULL,NULL,NULL,16,'\n   Region:&amp;nbsp;\n  \n      \n          National    \n     <h3>CLC&amp;rsquo;s Hassan Yussuff, &amp;ldquo;say no to Colombia free trade pact&amp;rdquo;</h3>\n<p>OTTAWA &amp;ndash; The Canadian Labour Congress and affiliated unions joined people from human rights, church and community organizations on Parliament Hill on June 10th to protest against the Ottawa visit of Colombian president Alvaro Uribe and the free trade agreement that he is desperate to promote with Canada.</p>\n<fieldset class=&quot;fieldgroup group-issue&quot;><legend>Related Content</legend>\n   Related Issue:&amp;nbsp;\n  \n      \n          Free Trade with Colombia    \n       \n          Globalization, International Economy    \n     </fieldset>\n<p><a href=&quot;http://www.canadianlabour.ca/national/news/citizens-protest-colombian-president-s-visit-ottawa&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;>read more</a></p>',1348939096,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Wed, 10 Jun 2009 04:00:00 +0000',NULL,NULL,NULL,'\n   Region:&amp;nbsp;\n  \n      \n          National    \n     <h3>CLC&amp;rsquo;s Hassan Yussuff, &amp;ldquo;say no to Colombia free trade pact&amp;rdquo;</h3>\n<p>OTTAWA &amp;ndash; The Canadian Labour Congress and affiliated unions joined people from human rights, church and community organizations on Parliament Hill on June 10th to protest against the Ottawa visit of Colombian president Alvaro Uribe and the free trade agreement that he is desperate to promote with Canada.</p>\n<fieldset class=&quot;fieldgroup group-issue&quot;><legend>Related Content</legend>\n   Related Issue:&amp;nbsp;\n  \n      \n          Free Trade with Colombia    \n       \n          Globalization, International Economy    \n     </fieldset>\n<p><a href=&quot;http://www.canadianlabour.ca/national/news/citizens-protest-colombian-president-s-visit-ottawa&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;>read more</a></p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,'none',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Posted','269','News','News',NULL),(637,0,0,'Georgetti says EI must be improved','text/html','http://www.canadianlabour.ca/national/news/georgetti-says-ei-must-be-improved','their families and communities from suffering fallout from the worst economic crisis in a generation;Canada',NULL,NULL,342,NULL,NULL,NULL,16,'\n   Region:&amp;nbsp;\n  \n      \n          National    \n     <h3>CLC President says unemployment is ravaging families and communities</h3>\n<p>OTTAWA - The Employment Insurance program must be improved to prevent tens of thousands of workers, their families and communities from suffering fallout from the worst economic crisis in a generation, says Canadian Labour Congress President Ken Georgetti.</p>\n<fieldset class=&quot;fieldgroup group-issue&quot;><legend>Related Content</legend>\n   Related Issue:&amp;nbsp;\n  \n      \n          Jobs &amp; Economy    \n       \n          Unemployment Insurance    \n     \n   Related Human Rights &amp;amp; Equality:&amp;nbsp;\n  \n      \n          Young Workers    \n     </fieldset>\n<p><a href=&quot;http://www.canadianlabour.ca/national/news/georgetti-says-ei-must-be-improved&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;>read more</a></p>',1348939099,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Fri, 05 